The paper presents a fast tensor-based approach for detecting hidden overlapping communities under the Mixed Membership Stochastic Blockmodel (MMSB). This involves optimization techniques and sparse linear algebraic operations. The paper also mentions the applicability of the tensor method for unsupervised learning of a wide range of latent variable models. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SD (Sound), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
